---
// layout
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { getGeneratedOgImage } from "@utils/og-image";

const lastUpdated = "Jul 2026";
const ogImage = getGeneratedOgImage("pages", "now");
---

<PageLayout
  tabTitle="Now"
  description="What I'm focused on at this point in my life."
  image={ogImage}
>
  <section>
    <h1>/now</h1>
    <p class="hero-text">
      A list of things I'm focused on at this point in my life.
    </p>
    <p class="updated-date">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>OrbitBudget crossed 100 users:</strong> people are actually using
        it, and telling me what's wrong with it, which is even better. Going through
        the feedback and building the most-asked-for stuff, though not everything
        makes the cut. Orbit's whole point is staying simple. Some proper graphs and
        reports, though, turned out to be non-negotiable.
      </li>
      <li>
        Reading Kautilya's Arthashastra, half the time I have no idea what I'm
        reading, but it's fascinating
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The search for the next challenge:</strong> Actively applying for
        new roles. Building OrbitBudget has reignited my creative energy and taught
        me so much about product thinking. I'm eager to bring that momentum to a new
        team and a meaningful project.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Feeding the movie buff:</strong> striking off one movie a week from
        my watchlist.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <blockquote>
      <h3>Wait, what is this?</h3>
      <p>
        It's a concept popularized by{" "}
        <a href="https://sive.rs/nowff" target="_blank">
          Derek Sivers &#x2197;
        </a>. A /now page shares what you'd tell a friend you hadn't seen for a
        while.
      </p>
    </blockquote>
  </section>

  <style>
    .updated-date {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: var(--text-light);
      font-style: italic;
    }
  </style>
</PageLayout>
